{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ec862e0b-7384-4734-85da-5054b1f2d4f0","content":"**Starting with MSTest.Sdk 4.0.0, the default test runner switched from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform.** This means `vstest.console` can no longer discover or run your tests because the VSTest adapter/infrastructure is no longer wired up by default.\n\nYou have two options:\n\n**Option 1 — Migrate your CI to `dotnet test`** (recommended):\n```bash\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj\n```\n`dotnet test` automatically uses the new Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner.\n\n**Option 2 — Re-enable VSTest compatibility** by adding this to your `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>false</EnableMSTestRunner>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\nSetting `EnableMSTestRunner` to `false` restores the classic VSTest adapter so `vstest.console` works again.\n\n**Option 1 is the recommended path forward** — Microsoft.Testing.Platform is faster, supports parallel execution natively, and is the actively developed runner.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5a90b7b7-1e3e-4532-b368-d075d9dcae6d","outputTokens":274},"id":"338dc018-9099-40c6-ba33-cdf198d97c5d","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:06:22.086Z","parentId":"d3b427ba-9e59-46f5-8fd9-dedb19d12fca"}
